    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix redundant computation in PRACH processing\n\n### Summary\nThe rx_prach0 function was performing redundant structure member accesses when calling get_prach_prb_offset. The function assigned prach_ConfigIndex from structure members but then accessed the same members again in the function call instead of using the local variable.\n\nThis fix eliminates the redundant accesses by using the already assigned local variables, improving efficiency without changing functionality.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/prach.c`: \n  - Line 110: Changed from `fp->prach_emtc_config_common.prach_ConfigInfo.prach_ConfigIndex[ce_level]` to `prach_ConfigIndex`\n  - Line 122: Changed from `fp->prach_config_common.prach_ConfigInfo.prach_ConfigIndex` to `prach_ConfigIndex`\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high PRACH processing load, the redundant structure accesses could be observed in profiling data as unnecessary memory reads. The fix reduces the number of structure member accesses per PRACH processing call.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Run OAI eNB with PRACH enabled\n2. Generate PRACH traffic from multiple UEs\n3. Profile the rx_prach0 function using a performance analyzer\n4. Observe reduced memory access patterns after applying the fix\n\n"
}